as i want to have a real test, i have try to update a copy of our 4.5.10 production oc server to 5.0.5. after updating, when i take a look on the  mysql db, i still have all of ours ldap users on oc_user_database (326 users). i can log with my ldap account and i'm still administrator. but, when i want to display users on oc admin page, i can see only 30 users.

as demonstration, i have log a short session with my ldap admin account in debug mode. i just log in and go to the "users" page to display these one. i had also try to go to the bottom and force display and just log out after. so, you can see owncloud.log at the end of message.

our owncloud server configuration:
- a wheezy (debian 7) xen virtual server
- owncloud from opensuze debian_6.0 repository
- php5 from wheezy (5.4.4-14)
- mysql-server-5.5 from wheezy (5.5.30+dfsg-1.1)

our ldap server:
- a lenny (debian 5) xen virtual server
- openldap from lenny (2.4.11-1+lenny2.1)

